    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A Study on Consumer Satisfaction with Special Reference to Double Horse Rice Products of Manjilas Group of Companies Pvt Ltd</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Sreejesh Rajan</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Consumer Satisfaction with Special Reference<br />Manjilas Group of Companies</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">May-2012 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P5662</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">This is the project that I have done in MANJILAS FOOD TECH LTD. I did the project on the topic consumer satisfaction. Consumers are the kings of marketing now a days. Up to this market era consumers are not considered in marketing. But in this time consumers have also a great part in marketing. The vast majority of gourmet food and beverage companies are small businesses. Many began as cottage outfits operating out of the homes or farms of the owners. Many of these firms are local or regional in scale, while others have a national reputation but poor national distribution.
Consumer is treated as the king of today's marketing. The whole production of every organizations are directed to the needs and preferences of consumers. With out consumers a business cannot survive. So in order to capture the consumers from a very competitive market, the marketer much emphasis on satisfying the consumers. He needs to identify the taste and preferences of consumers, i.e. products or services offered by the market should satisfying the consumers other wise the consumers may shift over to the other organization. Only satisfied consumers can bring benefit to the organization. Many companies are aiming for big satisfaction, because consumers who are just satisfied still find it easy to switch when a better offer comes along. Those who are highly satisfied are much less ready to switch.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/9904">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/9904</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/9711">MBA-2012</a><br/></td></tr>
</table></center><br/>
